E. Network Namespace

To isolate the container from Host server, we create a namespace for the containers.
If we have 4 containers in the host and each container will be in different namespace.
First the containers are isolated now and can't reach the host server due to the network is differnt.

Now each container from different namespace has to communicate each other, create a network switch and namespace can connect to network switch.

Container can reach the LAN network with only the help of Ethernet network.
Network switch can reach out to ethernet network with the help of Network switch interface.


Container ---> Network switch ---> Network switch interface ---> Ethernet0 ----> Lan Network ---> Internet or Other system.


C 192.150.15.2 ---> NS 192.150.15.0 ---> NSI 192.150.15.5 ----> E0 192.150.10.2 ---> LAN 192.150.10.0 ----> Other System 192.150.10.3

Note: Host server 192.150.10.1



F. Docker Networking
None Netowrk: Docker created in the host doesn't have a IP address for the container. Only host will be having an IP address.
                 Docker cannot reach any network. From any network we cannot reach a docker container.
                 Only for the testing reason we can create this container.

Host Network: Docker will have a connetivity with host network. Host = 192.150.10.0 and container = 192.150.10.1
              We cannot create a another container due to the container port 80 is accessed from host network is standard.
              curl https://192.150.10.0:80/ 


Bridge Network: Bridge network is used to connnect mulitple containers within the same network. 
                Container can reach bridge network via cable from container and reach the cable from bridge network interface.
                Bridge network interface will connect to the ethernet0. Eth0 ---> Host network


Note: 
Create network namespace for a container.
Create bridge network/interface
Create veth cable
Attach one end veth cable to namespace
Attach other end veth cable to bridge network
Assign the IP address
Bring the interfaces up
Enable NAT-IP Masquerade



